Strategy B: CFI≥0.5 AND freq<60)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) will:\r\n- De-weight constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1 → score≈1.0 but freq component <1)\r\n- Preserve research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5 → higher combined score)\r\n- Distinguish \"truly informative\" from \"metaprogramming artifacts\"\r\n\r\n## Method\r\nSame 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare precision/recall against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nHigher precision with acceptable recall - separating causal patterns from format noise\r\n\r\n## Results\r\n[TODO: Run experiment]\r\nfile: experiments/hybrid_scoring_experiment.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:00:23\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379024763}}
